The paper deals with problems related to clustering and covering points in a metric space, which are fundamental topics in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the online versions of these problems in higher dimensions, using the $L_\infty$ norm. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT).
